<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[796,1394,1410,1833]" pageId="55" pageNumber="334">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1843" box="[801,904,1581,1596]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Macrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Macrotus</taxonomicName>
bucharensis 1S in subgenus Blanfordimys. The name 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1387,1607,1636]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Phaiomys">Microtus (Phaiomys)</taxonomicName>
bucharensis has priority over the still widely used name 
<taxonomicName box="[968,1079,1682,1715]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microtus</taxonomicName>
bucharicus by B. S. Vinogradov in 1931. Morphologically and genetically, it is sister species to M. af ghanus. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="334" type="synonymic_list">
